  "prompt": "What is a short circuit, and what is short circuiting (in simple English)?",
  "response": "A **short circuit** is an electrical problem that occurs when electricity flows along an unintended path, often due to a flaw in the wiring. This can happen when two wires touch each other, bypassing the normal component that they\u2019re supposed to go through, which can cause a lot of current to flow suddenly. This can lead to overheating, damage, or even fires.\n\n**Short circuiting** is the action of creating a short circuit. It means the electricity is taking a shortcut instead of following the proper route. This can be dangerous because it can lead to overheating and potentially cause a failure or fire in electrical devices or systems.",
